ðŸ”¥ Why systemd does this (official Red Hat explanation)

On RHEL7 with systemd version 219, if any filesystem fails to unmount during a reboot, systemd considers the reboot unsafe and converts the operation into a full shutdown.

This behavior is documented by Red Hat:

â€œsystemctl reboot results in shutdown when a mount cannot be unmountedâ€

Ref: Red Hat Solutions 3323251, 3407891

Bugzilla: 1212199



